installation of UV in terminal:

  uv --version

macOS / Linux:  curl  -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh
Windows (PowerShell): powershell -ExecutionPolicy ByPass -c "irm https://astral.sh/uv/install.ps1 | iex"


installation of git in MAC OS and windows 

macOS Installation
1. Open Terminal: Press Cmd + Space, type Terminal, press Enter.
2. Install Git: Type: git --version and press Enter. Click Install if prompted.
3. Verify Installation: Type: git --version
4. Configure Name and Email (one-time setup):
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@email.com"
5. Test Git:
git init test
cd test
git status

Windows Installation
1. Download Git: Visit https://git-scm.com/download/win
2. Run Installer: Open the file and click Next until Install.
3. Open Git Bash: Start Menu > Search Git Bash > Open.
4. Verify Installation: Type: git --version
5. Configure Name and Email (one-time setup):
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@email.com"
6. Test Git:
git init test
cd test
git status

How to Create an OpenAI API Key
This guide explains how to generate and use an OpenAI API key for development and AI tools.
Step 1: Open OpenAI Platform
Open your browser and go to: https://platform.openai.com
Step 2: Sign In
Log in using your Google account, Microsoft account, or email and password.
Step 3: Go to API Keys Page
After login, click your profile icon in the top-right corner.
Select 'View API keys' from the menu.
Step 4: Create a New API Key
Click the button: 'Create new secret key'.
Copy the generated key and store it securely.
Step 5: Save Your API Key
Important: You will not be able to view the full key again.
Save it in a password manager or secure file.
Step 6: Set API Key in Your System
For macOS / Linux (Terminal):
export OPENAI_API_KEY="your_api_key_here"
For Windows (PowerShell):
setx OPENAI_API_KEY "your_api_key_here"
Step 7: Test Your API Key
Use your API key in your application or tool to verify it works correctly.


